Definition: from {{h539}}; established, i.e. (figuratively) trusty; also (abstractly) trustworthiness; faith(-ful), truth.
of Egyptian derivation; used only as an adjunct of {{h4996}}; Amon (i.e. Ammon or Amn), a deity of Egypt; multitude, populous.
from the same as {{h517}}; a collection, i.e. community of persons; nation, people.
the same as {{h520}}; Ammah, a hill in Palestine; Ammah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h520}}; cubit.

prolonged from {{h517}}; properly, a mother (i.e. unit of measure, or the fore-arm (below the elbow), i.e. a cubit; also a door-base (as a bond of the entrance); cubit, + hundred (by exchange for {{h3967}}), measure, post.
a variation for {{h1995}}; a throng of people; multitude.
the same as {{h525}}; Amon, the name of three Israelites; Amon.
from {{h539}}, probably in the sense of training; like {{h542}}; skilled, i.e. an architect; one brought up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h523}}; nation.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h639}} (only in the plural as a singular); the face; face, visage.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h597}}; figuratively, to distress; trouble.
a primitive root; to breathe hard, i.e. be enraged; be angry (displeased).
a primitive root; to mourn, i.e. complain; complain.
to insist; compel.
probably from an unused root meaning to be narrow; according to most a plumb-line, and to others a hook; plumb-line
sometimes, אָנֹכִי; a primitive pronoun; I; I, me, × which.
from {{h578}}; groaning; lamentation, sorrow.
from {{h578}} and {{h5971}}; groaning of (the) people; Aniam, an Israelite; Aniam.
probably from {{h579}} (in the sense of conveyance); a ship or (collectively) a fleet; galley, navy (of ships).
feminine of {{h590}}; a ship; ship(-men).
from {{h408}} and {{h7843}}; 'Thou must not destroy'; probably the opening words to a popular song; Al-taschith.
a primitive word; a mother (as the bond of the family); in a wide sense (both literally and figuratively [like father]); dam, mother, × parting.
or (more properly) אֶלְתְּקֵה; of uncertain derivation; Eltekeh or Elteke, a place in Palestine; Eltekeh.
from {{h410}} and {{h8626}}; God (is) straight; Eltekon, a place in Palestine; Eltekon.
patrial from a name of uncertain derivation; an Elkoshite or native of Elkosh; Elkoshite.
probably from {{h410}} and a masculine form of {{h8435}} (compare {{h8434}}); God (is) generator; Eltolad, a place in Palestine; Eltolad.
probably from {{h408}} and {{h6965}}; a non-rising (i.e. resistlessness); no rising up.
from {{h410}} and {{h7069}}; God has obtained; Elkanah, the name of several Israelites; Elkanah.

a primitive particle; used very widely as demonstrative, lo!; interrogative, whether?; or conditional, if, although; also Oh that!, when; hence, as a negative, not; (and, can-, doubtless, if, that) (not), + but, either, + except, + more(-over if, than), neither, nevertheless, nor, oh that, or, + save (only, -ing), seeing, since, sith, + surely (no more, none, not), though, + of a truth, + unless, + verily, when, whereas, whether, while, + yet.
apparently a primitive word; a maid-servant or female slave; (hand-) bondmaid(-woman), maid(-servant).
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of {{h4975}}; well-loined (i.e. burly) or mighty; terrible.
or אָנָה; contracted from {{h370}}; where?; hence, whither?, when?; also hither and thither; any (no) whither, now, where, whither(-soever).
(Aramaic) or אֲנָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h589}}; I; I, as for me.
or אָנָּה; apparent contracted from {{h160}} and {{h4994}}; oh now!; I (me) beseech (pray) thee, O.
time past, i.e.; yesterday or last night; former time, yesterday(-night)
contracted from {{h539}}; stability; (figuratively) certainty, truth, trustworthiness; assured(-ly), establishment, faithful, right, sure, true (-ly, -th), verity.
from {{h4969}}; properly, something expansive, i.e. a bag; sack.
from {{h571}}; veracious; Amittai, an Israelite; Amittai.
a primitive root; to groan; lament, mourn.
a primitive root (perhaps rather identical with {{h578}} through the idea of contraction in anguish); to approach; hence, to meet in various senses; befall, deliver, happen, seek a quarrel.
contracted from {{h595}}; I; I, (as for) me, mine, myself, we, × which, × who.
probably from the same root as {{h5170}}; a gorge or narrow pass; Anacharath, a place in Palestine; Anaharath.
(Aramaic) or (feminine) אִנִּיןlemma אֵנִּין first vowel, corrected to אִנִּין; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h1992}}; they; × are, them, these.
contracted for {{h587}}; we; we.
the same as {{h582}}; Enosh, a son of Seth; Enos.

from {{h605}}; properly, a mortal (and thus differing from the more dignified {{h120}}); hence, a man in general (singly or collectively); another, × (blood-) thirsty, certain, chap(-man); divers, fellow, × in the flower of their age, husband, (certain, mortal) man, people, person, servant, some (× of them),   stranger, those,   their trade. It is often unexpressed in the English versions, especially when used in apposition with another word. Compare {{h376}}.
from {{h584}}; sighing; groaning, mourn, sigh.
a primitive root; to sigh; groan, mourn, sigh.
apparently from {{h595}}; we; ourselves, us, we.
(Aramaic) or אֲנַחְנָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h587}}; we; we.
from {{h410}} and {{h6213}}; God has made; Elasah, the name of four Israelites; Elasah, Eleasah.
denominative from {{h505}}; causative, to make a thousandfold; bring forth thousands.
a primitive root, to associate with; hence, to learn (and causatively to teach); learn, teach, utter.
prop, the same as {{h504}}; hence (the ox's head being the first letter of the alphabet, and this eventually used as a numeral) a thousand; thousand.
from {{h502}}; a family; also (from the sense of yoking or taming) an ox or cow; family, kine, oxen.
the same as {{h505}}; Eleph, a place in Palestine; Eleph.
(Aramaic) or אֶלֶף; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h505}}; thousand.
a primitive root; to press; urge.
from {{h410}} and {{h6466}}; God (is) act; Elpaal, an Israelite; Elpaal.
probably a patronymic from an unused name derived from {{h559}} in the sense of publicity, i.e. prominence; thus, a mountaineer; an Emorite, one of the Canaanitish tribes; Amorite.
from {{h564}}; Imri, the name of two Israelites; Imri.
or אֶמְרָה; feminine of {{h561}}, and meaning the same; commandment, speech, word.
from {{h559}}; talkative; Immer, the name of five Israelites; Immer.
(Aramaic) perhaps from {{h560}} (in the sense of bringing forth); a lamb; lamb.
the same as {{h561}}; promise, speech, thing, word.
from {{h559}}; something said; answer, × appointed unto him, saying, speech, word.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h559}}; command, declare, say, speak, tell.
of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation; Amraphel, a king of Shinar; Amraphel.
or prolonged אֲמַרְיָהוּ; from {{h559}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has said (i.e. promised); Amarjah, the name of nine Israelites; Amariah.
an orthographical variation of {{h551}}; in (very) deed; of a surety.

a primitive root; to be alert, physically (on foot) or mentally (in courage); confirm, be courageous (of good courage, stedfastly minded, strong, stronger), establish, fortify, harden, increase, prevail, strengthen (self), make strong (obstinate, speed).
or אֲמִינוֹן; from {{h539}}; faithful; Amnon (or Aminon), a son of David; Amnon.
adverb from {{h544}}; verily; indeed, no doubt, surely, (it is, of a) true(-ly, -th).
from {{h553}}; force; strength.
from {{h553}}; strong; Amtsi, an Israelite; Amzi.
probably from {{h553}}; of a strong color, i.e. red (others fleet); bay.
from {{h553}}; strength; stronger.
or אֲמַצְיָהוּ; from {{h553}} and {{h3050}}; strength of Jah; Amatsjah, the name of four Israelites; Amaziah.

a primitive root; to say (used with great latitude); answer, appoint, avouch, bid, boast self, call, certify, challenge, charge,   (at the, give) command(-ment), commune, consider, declare, demand, × desire, determine, × expressly, × indeed, × intend, name, × plainly, promise, publish, report, require, say, speak (against, of), × still, × suppose, talk, tell, term, × that is, × think, use (speech), utter, × verily, × yet.
the same as {{h548}}; Amanah, a mountain near Damascus; Amana.
feminine of {{h543}}; something fixed, i.e. a covenant. an allowance; certain portion, sure.
feminine of {{h544}} (in the specific sense of training); tutelage; brought up.
from {{h539}}; verity; truth.
feminine active participle of {{h544}} (in the original sense of supporting); a column; pillar.
feminine form of {{h544}} (in its usual sense); adverb, surely; indeed.
denominative from {{h3225}}; to take the right hand road; turn to the right. See {{h539}}.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h539}}; believe, faithful, sure.
from {{h539}}; sure; abstract, faithfulness; adverb, truly; Amen, so be it, truth.
from {{h539}} (in the sense of training); an expert; cunning workman.
from {{h517}}; gathering-spot; Amam, a place in Palestine; Amam.

a primitive root; (Isaiah 30:21; interchangeable with {{h541}}, to go to the right hand); properly, to build up or support; to foster as a parent or nurse; figuratively to render (or be) firm or faithful, to trust or believe, to be permanent or quiet; morally to be true or certain; hence, assurance, believe, bring up, establish,   fail, be faithful (of long continuance, stedfast, sure, surely, trusty, verified), nurse, (-ing father), (put), trust, turn to the right.
or (shortened) אֱמֻנָה; feminine of {{h529}}; literally firmness; figuratively security; morally fidelity; faith(-ful, -ly, -ness, (man)), set office, stability, steady, truly, truth, verily.
from {{h553}}; strong; Amots, an Israelite; Amoz.
an abbreviated form for {{h526}}; Ami, an Israelite; Ami.
or (shortened) אַמִּץ; from {{h553}}; strong or (abstractly) strength; courageous, mighty, strong (one).
apparently from {{h559}} (in the sense of self-exaltation); a summit (of a tree or mountain); bough, branch.
a primitive root; to droop; by implication to be sick, to mourn; languish, be weak, wax feeble.
from {{h535}}; sick; weak.
from {{h535}}; languid; feeble.
